place.name: THURNING
place.gazetteerText: THURNING, a parish in Aylsham district, Norfolk; 7½ miles NE of Elmham r. station. Post town, Foulsham, under Thetford. Acres, 1,584. Real property, £2,229. Pop., 178. Houses, 34. T. Hall is the seat of J. Gay, Esq. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £350.* Patron, Corpus Christi College, Cambridge. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
